### a. Class, object, constructor (__init__, self)

**Definition:** *A class is a blueprint; an object is an instance. `__init__` runs at creation; `self` refers to the current instance. In system design, classes model domain entities (User, Order, Account). DDD uses aggregates; ORMs (SQLAlchemy, Django) map classes to DB tables.*

