**Note:** In system design, classes model domain entities — User, Order, Account. DDD uses aggregates (cluster of entities). Each instance has identity and state. ORMs (SQLAlchemy, Django) map classes to DB tables.

### b. Instance attributes vs class attributes

**Definition:** *Instance: `self.attr` — per object. Class: `ClassName.attr` — shared by all instances.*

**Syntax:**
```
