| Term | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| **LLM** | Large Language Model — GPT, Claude, Llama. Takes text in, returns text out. |
| **RAG** | Retrieval-Augmented Generation — fetch relevant docs, inject into prompt, then generate. Reduces hallucination. |
| **Embedding** | Vector representation of text; used for semantic search. |
| **Fine-tuning** | Training a pre-trained model on your data. |
| **Prompt engineering** | Crafting input text to get better LLM output. |

### Web & Decentralized

| Term | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| **Web3** | Decentralized web — blockchains, smart contracts, wallets. Python: web3.py, Brownie. |
| **Smart Contract** | Code on blockchain (Solidity); Python used for testing, scripting. |
| **API** | Application Programming Interface — REST (HTTP), GraphQL, gRPC. |
| **Microservices** | Small, independent services; each has its own API. |

### Advanced Concepts

| Term | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| **Vector DB** | Stores embeddings for similarity search (Pinecone, Weaviate, pgvector). Used in RAG. |
| **Orchestration** | Scheduling and coordinating workflows — Airflow, Prefect, Dagster. |
| **Event-Driven** | React to events (message in queue, file landed) rather than polling. |
| **Idempotency** | Same request twice = same result. Critical for retries. |
| **Observability** | Logs, metrics, traces — understanding what your system is doing. |

